<task id="WCWE-005" project="UI Create Wizard Enhancements R1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Fix double /api/api/ prefix in SprkChat context-mappings URL</title>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>1 hour</estimated-effort>
    <tags>frontend, bug-fix, pcf</tags>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Fix the double /api/api/ prefix in the SprkChat PCF control's context-mappings URL which causes
    a 404 Not Found. The request should use a single /api/ prefix so the URL resolves to
    {bffBaseUrl}/api/ai/chat/context-mappings (or whatever the correct BFF endpoint path is).
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior frontend developer with expertise in Fluent UI v9, React, and Dataverse Code Pages</role>

  <goal>
    The SprkChat context-mappings request uses the correct URL with a single /api/ prefix and returns
    HTTP 200.
  </goal>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">BFF API uses /api/ prefix for all endpoints; clients must not duplicate it.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-001-minimal-api.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      UAT feedback (E-13) found that the SprkChat control issues a request with a double /api/api/
      prefix, resulting in a 404. This is likely caused by the base URL already including /api/ and
      the client code prepending another /api/. A recent fix (commit 104301ac) addressed a similar
      double-prefix issue in speApiClient; this may be a remaining instance.
    </background>
    <dependencies />
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Locate the URL construction">Grep for context-mappings and /api/ai/chat in the SprkChat PCF control source to find the URL construction code.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Identify the double prefix cause">Determine whether the base URL already includes /api/ or whether the path literal duplicates it.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Fix the URL">Remove the duplicate /api/ prefix so the final URL is correct.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Search for similar issues">Grep for /api/api/ across the codebase to find any other double-prefix occurrences.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Build and verify">Build the SprkChat PCF control and confirm no compile errors.</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">SprkChat PCF control source file(s) containing the URL (to be identified in step 1)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Request to context-mappings endpoint returns HTTP 200 (not 404).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">grep -r "/api/api/" src/ returns zero results.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">SprkChat PCF control builds without errors.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
